news.title: Mumbai: Stop-work notice to Bhendi Bazaar redevelopment project revoked
news.para: The Rs 4,000-crore project was brought to a standstill when the BMC followed up on deputy CM Devendra Fadnavis ordering an inquiry into complaints that the Saifee Burhani Upliftment Trust, which is executing the project, had changed the original plans.

news.title: Dubious funds from Chinese entities sent to Telangana-based granite entities: ED
news.para: ED launched the searches at the offices and residential premises of Swetha Granites, Swetha Agencies, Sri Venkateshwara Granites, PSR Granites, Arvind Granites, Giriraj Shipping Agencies & their related entities in Karimnagar & Hyderabad.

news.title: Bank of Baroda lowers home loan rates by 25 basis points to 8.25%
news.para: ​At 8.25 per cent, BoB's rate is lower than that of the segmental leaders SBI and HDFC, whose new pricing is at 8.40 per cent, announced before Diwali and lasting end-December.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires two land parcels in Noida for Rs 377 crore
news.para: “The Noida authority will earn Rs 377 crore from the auction and this will attract investment of Rs 2,000 crore,” Noida authority said in a statement.

news.title: Gurugram: 40 building sites flout GRAP rules, penalised Rs 20 lakh
news.para: ​A fine of Rs 50,000 has been imposed on each developer and if they fail to deposit, the same will be recovered during the grant of occupation certificate.

news.title: GNIDA asks Jaiprakash Associates to remove helipad at Jaypee Greens
news.para: The residents’ association of Jaypee Greens had moved the Allahabad high court earlier this year against the helipad operating within a residential colony of both villas and highrises.

news.title: RERA scam in Kalyan Dombivli: 16 more bank accounts frozen
news.para: ​The police said that earlier they had frozen 40 bank accounts which now makes the total to 56. The financial trail into these accounts is underway, sources informed TOI.

news.title: Repco Home Finance's net profit dips 17.19% in Q2 FY23
news.para: The company's net consolidated income stood at Rs 317.58 crore in Q2 FY23, a dip of 5.06 per cent from Rs 334.50 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Land for Evergrande's headquarters in Shenzhen put up for auction
news.para: The sale of the 10,000 square meter (2.47 acres)land will be held between Nov 21 to 26, according to the notice, which says the construction at the site have been halted since September 2021.

news.title: Kamdhenu's net profit up 9.18% in Q2 FY23
news.para: "We have raised funds to the tune of ~ Rs. 70 crore. This will help to reduce our debt and make us debt free. This will also help create a better brand position in the industry," said Satish Kumar Agarwal, chairman & MD, Kamdhenu.

news.title: CM aims at making Odisha slum-free by 2023, launches land survey using drones
news.para: The land survey was taken in Bhubaneswar, Cuttack, Berhampur, Rourkela and Sambalpur civic body areas under the state government's 'Jaga Mission' programme.

news.title: Vipul posts net profit of Rs 18.67 crore in Q2 FY23
news.para: Anil Kumar Tibrewal,CFO of Vipul, has resigned due to personal reasons. The board of directors have approved the scheme of amalgamation of Abhipra Trading, Graphic Research Consultants India, United Buildwell, Vineeta Trading and Vipul Eastern Infracon with Vipul.

news.title: Development of Noida airport on schedule, within budget: Top project officer
news.para: The greenfield airport is coming up in the Jewar area of western Uttar Pradesh's Gautam Buddh Nagar district, around 75 km from Delhi, and will be the second international airport in the National Capital Region (NCR).

news.title: With nine managing directors in eight years, Bhopal Metro project in slow lane
news.para: Unified Metropolitan Transport Authority for Bhopal metro is still awaited. It would lead to integration, planning and regulation of different commuting modes. Bhopal-based SPA has been roped in to cater to the influence area of the project.

news.title: Gurugram: Construction zone since 2019, no way to escape dust at Atul Kataria Chowk
news.para: It connects the city’s residents to Dwarka Expressway, the railway station, the bus stand, the Maruti manufacturing plant on the Old Palam Gurugram road, Kapashera border, Sheetla Mata temple, Signature Towers, and other residential and commercial hubs.
